<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-26T06:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-26T06:35:00-05:00" n="1429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1429">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.6791/3</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-26T15:00:00+03:25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1915, 3 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 28, 9.15 a.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Turkish Ambassador has returned and resumed charge of Turkish Embassy.
                            German Minister being yet in Persia with apparently no intention of
                            leaving, I have to suggest that our flag and protection of this
                            Government should be withdrawn from the German Legation until such a
                            time as Russian forces actually enter Teheran, but that German subjects
                            be allowed to remain here at the Legation of the United States. Instruct
                            by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CJL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>